                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Canni5 is 3 minute recast, not 69 seconds. PVP Does not apply to cannibalize either, so while cannibalize 4 is 148hp for 82 mana (and canni 5 is 1924hp for 1066 mana). Seduction of Saryrn is around 42 hit points for 50 mana, and continues to work no matter what you're doing.<br /><br />As many people have said, Active Mana Regen &lt;&lt;&lt; Passive. Shamans can't do anything else while generating mana. In theory, if all a shaman did was cannibalize, he could get very nice mana regen, but in practice it wouldn't be possible, because there would be no time to spend the mana on anything.<br /><br />POP really wasn't a good expansion for shamans. Not only did they add slow mitigation, but they went even further and gave Beastlords a 65% slow. Sure, that 10% might seem like a lot, but if a mob has 50% slow mitigation, Turgurs is a 37.5% slow and Sha's Revenge is 32.5%. The difference then hardly accounts for shit. So when you're doing LDoN, or Elemental planes, do you want a superior slower with "okayish" DPS, or a "Good Enough" Slower with superior (130+) DPS who gives the group almost identical buffs, as well as 9 mana a tick? POP was a bit kinder to necros with trash mobs having significantly more hit points (longer fights = more potential damage), but really the only good thing shamans got was quiescence, and Virulent Paralysis.</span id="msg"></font></td>
